The evidence with the title 'Did the 2008 tax rebates stimulate spending? ' says More than two-thirds of the $152 billion bill consisted of economic stimulus payments to be sent beginning in may to approximately 130 million households . To qualify , recipients  ... Debt with the rebate . Hence, the most common plan for the rebate is to use it to pay off debt , and only one-fifth plan to mostly spend the rebate . 
